This paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category as it deals with deep reinforcement learning and its robustness to attacks. It could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category as it involves the study of intelligent agents and their ability to adapt to adversarial conditions. The paper also discusses the vulnerability of deep RL to attacks, which could place it in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks in RL could place it in the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. Finally, the study of RL agents and their ability to adapt to changing environments could also place it in the Robotics (cs.RO) category.
